Name:
* Aye Khine Nan MYA disqualified for doping. 




Women's Flyweight - Weightlifting - Athens 2004 Summer Olympics
Event Format:
     
     In weightlifting the total score for a lifter was the sum of the lifter's result in the snatch and the clean & jerk categories. Three lifts was allowed in each category. In case of a tie, the lighter lifter won. Lifters without a valid snatch score did not perform the clean & jerk category. Event facts: Women's Flyweight competition was held at the Nikaia Weightlifting Hall and 15 athletes participated in the event.

Name:
* Izabela Dragneva BUL disqualified for doping. 




Women's Flyweight - Weightlifting - Sydney 2000 Summer Olympics
Event Format:
     
     Athletes competed in two types of lift: the snatch, in which they raised the bar over the head in one movement, and the clean & jerk, in which they raised the bar i two movements using the combined strength of arms and legs. Each athlete was allowed three attempts at each type of lift. The best result in each type of lift counted in the final score for the athlete.  Event facts: Women's Flyweight competition was held at the Sydney Convention Centre, Darling Harbour and 12 athletes participated in the event.
